<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="269" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1809,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1845,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">Description.</emphasis>
Specimen is cushion-shaped, white (fixed specimen) (
<figureCitation box="[966,1035,1845,1870]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1032,1054]" captionTargetBox="[188,1399,265,1010]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[188,1400,265,1011]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Photographs of sponges: A. Hymedesmia (Hymedesmia) pansa, B. Chalinula renieroides, C. Haliclona (Halichoclona) fulva, D. Haliclona (Rhizoniera) rosea, E. Ircinia variabilis (scale bar: for A = 20 cm, B = 20 cm, C = 15 cm, D = 10 cm, E = 25 cm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264013/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">
Fig. 
<number box="[1020,1035,1846,1870]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Sponge surface is covered nonerected oval pores. The sponge tissue is soft and fragile. Spongin is scarce. Skeleton has a hymedesmoid arrangement. Ectosomal spicules composed of 
<number box="[685,727,1918,1942]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
bundles of tornotes comprise a column. Skeleton (
<figureCitation box="[1307,1374,1917,1942]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1587,1609]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,193,1564]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[188,1398,193,1565]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Skeleton networks of sponges: A. Hymedesmia (Hymedesmia) pansa, B. Chalinula renieroides, C. Haliclona (Halichoclona) fulva, D. Haliclona (Rhizoniera) rosea E. Ircinia variabilis: 1. secondary fibres, 2. primary fibrils, 3. thin filaments. (Scale bar: for A = 150 µm, B = 180 µm, C = 150 µm, D = 130 µm, E 1, 2 = 100 µm, E 3 = 120 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264014/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">
Fig. 
<number box="[1361,1374,1918,1942]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
A) of the ectosome consists of brushes of tornotes. Choanosomal spicules comprise megascleres (tornotes and acanthostyles) and microscleres (isochelae). Tornotes are slender and straight (subtylo) (
<number box="[1148,1248,1990,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" value="205.0" valueMax="220.0" valueMin="190.0">190–220</number>
<date box="[1255,1319,1990,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">
x 
<number box="[1277,1319,1990,2014]" pageId="1" pageNumber="268" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
</date>
µm) (
<figureCitation box="[1390,1436,1989,2014]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1391,1413]" captionTargetBox="[302,1282,489,1362]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[296,1290,483,1369]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Spicules of sponges: A. Hymedesmia (Hymedesmia) pansa: 1. straight (subtylo) tornotes, 2. acanthostyles, 3. arcuate isochelae, B. Chalinula renieroides: curved oxeas, C. Haliclona (Halichoclona) fulva: fusiform oxeas, D: Haliclona (Rhizoniera) rosea: oxeas (Scale bar: A 1 = 30 µm, A 2 = 30 µm, A 3 = 10 µm, B = 20 µm, C = 40 µm, D = 25 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264015/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="268">Fig.</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,213]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">
<number box="[151,167,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" value="4.0">4</number>
A 
<number box="[192,202,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" value="1.0">1</number>
). Acanthostyles (
<number box="[396,482,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" value="150.0" valueMax="220.0" valueMin="80.0">80–220</number>
<date box="[489,552,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">
x 
<number box="[510,552,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" value="6.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="4.0">4–8</number>
</date>
µm) are obviously spined along the whole length (
<figureCitation box="[1126,1193,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1391,1413]" captionTargetBox="[302,1282,489,1362]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[296,1290,483,1369]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Spicules of sponges: A. Hymedesmia (Hymedesmia) pansa: 1. straight (subtylo) tornotes, 2. acanthostyles, 3. arcuate isochelae, B. Chalinula renieroides: curved oxeas, C. Haliclona (Halichoclona) fulva: fusiform oxeas, D: Haliclona (Rhizoniera) rosea: oxeas (Scale bar: A 1 = 30 µm, A 2 = 30 µm, A 3 = 10 µm, B = 20 µm, C = 40 µm, D = 25 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264015/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">
Fig. 
<number box="[1178,1193,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A 
<number box="[1216,1231,152,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" value="2.0">2</number>
). Microscleres are arcuate isochelae (
<number box="[358,429,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" value="15.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="10.0">10–20</number>
µm) with flattened shaft (
<figureCitation box="[722,789,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1391,1413]" captionTargetBox="[302,1282,489,1362]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[296,1290,483,1369]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Spicules of sponges: A. Hymedesmia (Hymedesmia) pansa: 1. straight (subtylo) tornotes, 2. acanthostyles, 3. arcuate isochelae, B. Chalinula renieroides: curved oxeas, C. Haliclona (Halichoclona) fulva: fusiform oxeas, D: Haliclona (Rhizoniera) rosea: oxeas (Scale bar: A 1 = 30 µm, A 2 = 30 µm, A 3 = 10 µm, B = 20 µm, C = 40 µm, D = 25 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/264015/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="269">
Fig. 
<number box="[774,789,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
A 
<number box="[811,823,188,212]" pageId="2" pageNumber="269" value="3.0">3</number>
) and no sigmas.
</paragraph>
